Gauge Charts
Use gauge charts to track progress along a single measure, such as how much revenue has been realized versus the target.

Create a Gauge Chart
In the lens, click  and then select the Polar Gauge (round) chart type.
A gauge (angular) and flat gauge (linear) are also available.
To compare the measure across every member of a category, like every account owner, add the dimension in the Trellis field.
To rank the performance based on the measure, sort the measure in ascending or descending order.

For example, set the Trellis Type field to Wrap so the chart can be viewed all at once, without having to scroll.
Also, set the bins in Conditional Formatting to create band colors.
The breakpoints set the range values where the color bands transition.
